InspireDaily Privacy Policy

Last Updated: July 14, 2024

InspireDaily ("we", "us", "our") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application ("App") and website ("Website"). By accessing or using InspireDaily, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with these terms, please do not use our App or Website.

1. Information We Collect

1.1 Personal Information
We may collect personal information that you provide to us directly, such as your name, email address, and account details when you create an account, contact us, or participate in any interactive features of the App or Website.

1.2 Usage Data
We may automatically collect information about your use of the App and Website, such as your IP address, device type, operating system, browser type, access times, and the pages you have viewed directly before and after accessing the App or Website.

1.3 Cookies and Similar Technologies
We may use cookies and similar tracking technologies to track the activity on our App and Website and hold certain information. Cookies are files with a small amount of data that are stored on your device.

2. How We Use Your Information

We may use the information we collect in the following ways:

2.1 To Provide and Maintain Our Service
To provide, operate, and maintain our App and Website.

2.2 To Improve Our Service
To understand and analyze how you use our App and Website, and to develop new products, services, features, and functionality.

2.3 To Communicate with You
To communicate with you, either directly or through one of our partners, including for customer service, to provide you with updates and other information relating to the App, and for marketing and promotional purposes.

2.4 To Process Your Transactions
To process transactions and to manage your orders.

2.5 To Personalize Your Experience
To personalize and improve your experience on our App and Website, including providing content and features that match your interests and preferences.

2.6 To Comply with Legal Obligations
To comply with applicable laws, regulations, and legal processes.

3. How We Share Your Information

3.1 With Service Providers
We may share your information with third-party service providers to perform functions and process user data and to help provide our App and Website.

3.2 For Business Transfers
We may share or transfer your information in connection with, or during negotiations of, any merger, sale of company assets, financing, or acquisition of all or a portion of our business to another company.

3.3 With Your Consent
We may share your information with third parties if you give us consent to do so.

4. Security of Your Information

We use administrative, technical, and physical security measures to help protect your personal information. While we have taken reasonable steps to secure the personal information you provide to us, please be aware that despite our efforts, no security measures are perfect or impenetrable and no method of data transmission can be guaranteed against any interception or other type of misuse.

5. Your Data Protection Rights

Depending on your location, you may have the following rights regarding your personal information:

5.1 The right to access – You have the right to request copies of your personal information.

5.2 The right to rectification – You have the right to request that we correct any information you believe is inaccurate or complete information you believe is incomplete.

5.3 The right to erasure – You have the right to request that we erase your personal information, under certain conditions.

5.4 The right to restrict processing – You have the right to request that we restrict the processing of your personal information, under certain conditions.

5.5 The right to object to processing – You have the right to object to our processing of your personal information, under certain conditions.

5.6 The right to data portability – You have the right to request that we transfer the data that we have collected to another organization, or directly to you, under certain conditions.

6. Children's Privacy

InspireDaily does not knowingly collect or solicit any information from anyone under the age of 13. If we become aware that we have collected personal information from a child under age 13 without verification of parental consent, we will take steps to remove that information from our servers.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page. You are advised to review this Privacy
